==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amphid
<hw>Am"phid</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a`mfw</grk> both: cf. F. <ets>amphide</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A salt of the class formed by the combination of
an acid and a base, or by the union of two oxides, two sulphides,
selenides, or tellurides, as distinguished from a <contr>haloid</contr>
compound.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Berzelius.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

